 Career History



Business Unit Manager, Industrial Control Systems

                                    Current                


Kendrion NV


                  Kendrion NV engages in the development, manufacture, and marketing of electromagnetic components for industrial and automotive applications. It operates through the Automotive and Industrial divisions. The Automotive division segment includes developing, manufacturing, and marketing electromagnetic components, mechatronics solutions, and sound systems for applications and customers. The Industrial division offers developing and manufacturing electromagnetic and mechatronic systems and components for industrial applications in markets such as process automation, energy generation and distribution, medical and analytical equipment, transportation, and aerospace. The company was founded by Wilhelm Binder in 1911 and is headquartered in Zeist, the Netherlands.                





 Boards & Committees



Corporate Boards ▾




Member, Executive Committee

                    Current                  


Kendrion NV

                    Kendrion NV engages in the development, manufacture, and marketing of electromagnetic components for industrial and automotive applications. It operates through the Automotive and Industrial divisions. The Automotive division segment includes developing, manufacturing, and marketing electromagnetic components, mechatronics solutions, and sound systems for applications and customers. The Industrial division offers developing and manufacturing electromagnetic and mechatronic systems and components for industrial applications in markets such as process automation, energy generation and distribution, medical and analytical equipment, transportation, and aerospace. The company was founded by Wilhelm Binder in 1911 and is headquartered in Zeist, the Netherlands.                  




Director

                    Current                  


Kuhnke AG

                    Kuhnke AG operates as a holding company with interest in automotive industry. The company was founded in 1928 and is headquartered in Malente, Germany.                  





 Other Affiliations




              Robert Lewin is affiliated with
                            Kendrion NV, Kendrion NV, Kuhnke AG.
            




